==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Feeze
<hw>Feeze</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[For sense 1, cf. F.
<ets>visser</ets> to screw, <ets>vis</ets> screw, or 1st E.
<ets>feaze</ets>, v.t.: for sense 2, see <er>Feese</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To turn, as a screw.</def> <mark>[Scot]</mark>
<rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To beat; to chastise; to humble; to worry.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <altsp>[Written also <asp>feaze</asp>,
<asp>feize</asp>, <asp>pheese</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Beau. &
Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To feeze up</b></col>, <cd>to work into a passion.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feeze</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Feeze
<hw>Feeze</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Fretful excitement.
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> See <er>Feaze</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fehling</ent>⟦br⟧
